This paper discusses the theoretical analysis of imitation learning approaches, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on the value discrepancy of these approaches, which is related to reinforcement learning and control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
